ntenance%20problem.%20There%20were%20360%20passengers%20and%2010%20crew%20members%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20arranged%20for%20a%20different%20aircraft%20to%20take%20our%20customers%20to%20Denver%20Monday%20morning%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20United%20spokesperson%20added.%20The%20FAA%20said%20it%20will%20investigate%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20open%20door%20on%20a%20plane%20would%20be%20a%20very%20dangerous%20situation%2C%20so%20it%20makes%20sense%20that%20the%20pilots%20were%20cautious%20and%20diverted%20to%20the%20nearest%20airport.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDescending%20below%2010%2C000%20feet%20would%20also%20make%20the%20air%20on%20board%20breathable%20if%20the%20cabin%20had%20depressurized%20due%20to%20an%20opening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201974%2C%20a%20McDonnell%20Douglas%20DC-10%20operated%20by%20Turkish%20Airlines%20suffered%20a%20fault%20with%20a%20cargo%20door%20latch.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20led%20to%20an%20explosive%20decompression%2C%20which%20cut%20off%20critical%20controls%20and%20led%20to%20the%20deaths%20of%20all%20346%20people%20on%20board.%20It%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20deadliest%20aviation%20disasters%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20earlier%2C%20a%20cargo%20door%20on%20American%20Airlines%20Flight%2096%20broke%20off%20due%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-737-max-and-other-airliners-that-suffered-failures-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edesign%20flaw%20with%20the%20DC-10%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20rapid%20decompression%20caused%20the%20passenger%20cabin's%20floor%20to%20collapse%2C%20and%20eleven%20people%20were%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvancements%20in%20aviation%20safety%20and%20design%20mean%20such%20events%20are%20even%20rarer%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-passengers-diverted-due-to-faulty-door-sensor-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3